es/comments/730486777","html_url":"https://github.com/ludwig-ai/ludwig/issues/1013#issuecomment-730486777","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/ludwig-ai/ludwig/issues/1013","id":730486777,"node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDczMDQ4Njc3Nw==","user":{"login":"tgaddair","id":1742912,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE3NDI5MTI=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1742912?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/tgaddair","html_url":"https://github.com/tgaddair","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tgaddair/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tgaddair/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tgaddair/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tgaddair/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tgaddair/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tgaddair/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tgaddair/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tgaddair/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tgaddair/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2020-11-19T16:25:13Z","updated_at":"2020-11-19T18:03:40Z","author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"One other thing worth mentioning is that something like this should be doable programmatically using the [train_online](https://github.com/uber/ludwig/blob/master/ludwig/api.py#L530) API today.  Something like:\r\n\r\n```\r\ngenerator = LudwigModel(generator_config)\r\ndiscriminator = LudwigModel(discriminator_config)\r\n\r\nreal_samples = load_dataset()\r\n\r\nfor epoch in epochs:\r\n    synthetic_dataset = generate_random_noise()\r\n    generator.train_online(synthetic_dataset)\r\n\r\n    generated_samples = generator.predict(generate_random_noise())\r\n    combined_dataset = merge(generated_samples, real_samples)\r\n\r\n    discriminator.train_online(combined_dataset)\r\n```\r\n\r\nUsing this approach, the only missing piece at the moment is the custom loss function for the generator (and the decoder if you're using image or audio data), but this should be solvable.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/ludwig-ai/ludwig/issues/comments/730486777/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"tgaddair","id":1742912,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE3NDI5MTI=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1742912?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/tgaddair","html_url":"https://github.com/tgaddair","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tgaddair/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tgaddair/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tgaddair/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tgaddair/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tgaddair/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tgaddair/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tgaddair/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tgaddair/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tgaddair/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false}},{"id":4017207463,"node_id":"MDEyOkxhYmVsZWRFdmVudDQwMTcyMDc0NjM=","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/ludwig-ai/ludwig/issues/events/4017207463","actor":{"login":"tgaddair","id":1742912,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE3NDI5MTI=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1742912?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/tgaddair","html_url":"https://github.com/tgaddair","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tgaddair/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tgaddair/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tgaddair/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/tgaddair/starred{/owner}{/repo}",